						               													<description>As in the other games of the Activity family, the aim of the game is to guess as many words as possible in order to reach the finish line on the board first. The game is played in teams, and the words from the cards have to be described in one of three ways: drawing, pantomime, or describing the word in other words.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Differences to Activity: The active player has one minute to make his/her team guess the word from the card. If they are successful, they get to move the corresponding number of spaces on the board. If not, the other teams take terms making one guess, and if correct, get to move their pawn. (This replaces the rule from standard Activity, where the opponent teams can only take part in the guessing during 6-point-questions.)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
